    <font size="5">
     ASL: "Santa"
    </font>
   </span>
   <br/>
  </font>
 </h1>
 <p>
  <p>
   The sign for Santa Claus is based on his bushy white beard. 
	Hold a loose "CLAW" hand to your chin.  Bring it down in an arc to your 
	chest and touch the pinkie finger side of your hand to your chest.
   <br/>
   <br/>
   SANTA CLAUS:
  </p>
  <p>
   <img border="0" height="376" src="/images/santa1.jpg" width="300"/>
   <img border="0" height="376" src="/images/santa2.jpg" width="300"/>
   <img border="0" height="376" src="/images/santa3.jpg" width="300"/>
  </p>
  <p>
   <br/>
  </p>
  <hr align="left" color="#000000" size="1" width="50%"/>
  <p>
   Are there other ways to sign Santa Claus? Yes. There are quite a 
			few.  The one above is nice though since it is simple, it uses 
			only one hand (which lets me hold an eggnog in the other), and is 
			non-initialized (it doesn't use an "S" hand so people won't accuse 
			you of using Signed English, which, apparently would make you a bad 
			boy or girl and not get any presents).
  </p>
